page.title: 06Houses in Farcet
page.content: We went to{Farcet}and looked at the different kinds of houses. We saw thatched cottages, modern semi-detached houses, some council houses and one or two detached houses. Some of the houses were made of brick, some of concrete blocks and some of white-washed stone. Most of the bricks are the kind made in the brickyards near here. Nearly all the houses had wooden windows and some of the windows were very small. The roofs were thatched, or had tiles or slates on them. Most of the houses had gardens and some of them were quite large. Some of the houses had a few steps leading up to the front door.
